# AGENTS.md — Required Project Instructions

Before planning or writing code in this repo, read and follow `AGENTS.md`.

## How to apply it

1. **Global standards** — Always obey the Global Coding Standards (mobile-first UI, `0.0.0.0` binding, no local server runs, remote staging at `http://192.168.0.77:3001`, deploy via git push + webhook, no 5etools repo edits, etc.).
2. **Pick the right role** — Match the task to the appropriate agent (DevOps/DB, Backend/Socket.io, Frontend UI, VTT Engine, AI Integration) and follow that role's directives in addition to global standards.
3. **Multi-area tasks** — When work spans roles, apply every relevant section; do not ignore constraints from other agents.

## Quick reference

| Task area | Agent role |
|-----------|------------|
| Docker, Prisma, SQLite, compose | Agent 1 — DevOps & DB Architect |
| Express API, Socket.io, MCP, backup, auth | Agent 2 — Backend Engineer |
| React UI, character sheet, dice box, navigation | Agent 3 — Frontend UI Developer |
| Canvas, tokens, grid, fog of war | Agent 4 — VTT Engine Developer |
| AI subsystem, LLM streaming, reference data | Agent 5 — AI Integration Engineer |

When in doubt, re-read `AGENTS.md` rather than guessing project conventions.
